<DOC><DOCNO> AP890304-0047 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-04-89 0600EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a PM-WeatherpageWeather     03-04 0656</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0674</SECOND><HEAD>Snow Blankets Much Of Midwest; Temperatures Sent Plummeting in Texas</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Snow blanketed the Midwest today and a cold front senttemperatures plummeting in Texas and much of the Plains.   A blizzard warning was posted this morning in north-centralNebraska, while winter storm warnings extended from northern NewMexico across eastern and south-central Colorado, south-central andeastern South Dakota, much of Minnesota, Wisconsin, upper Michiganand northern lower Michigan.   Friday evening snowfalls across Wisconsin included 10 to 12inches in Brown and Waupaca counties and about 10 inches in Shawanoand Manitowoc counties.   More than 8 inches fell at Alpena, Mich., and strong windscreated drifts of 2 to 3 feet.   Snowfall in Minnesota included about 12 inches at Willmar, 10inches at Minneapolis-St. Paul and New Ulm, 9 inches at Rochester, 8inches at Pine City and 6 inches at St. Cloud.   A cold front brought low temperatures across northwest Texas, asthe mercury fell 20 degrees in an hour at Abilene, and 26 degrees inan hour at Amarillo and Childress.   The high temperature at Lubbock was 83 degrees, then fell to 30degrees during one hour.   Cold air and strong winds brought late evening wind chills to 30degrees below zero or colder in the northern and central Plains.   Freezing rain extended from much of lower Michigan acrossnorthern Indiana, southern Wisconsin, and northeast throughsouthwest Iowa.   Snow fell in northern lower Michigan, Upper Michigan, northernWisconsin, Minnesota, northwest Iowa, eastern and south-centralNorth Dakota, South Dakota, Nebraska, northern and western Kansas,northern New Mexico, Colorado and southeast Wyoming.   Thundershowers hit parts of Missouri, Iowa, Illinois and Indiana.   Thunderstorm winds gusted to 70 mph near Jenks, Okla., andnickel-size hail fell west of Edmond, Okla.   Today's forecast called for snow spreading from the central andsouthern Rockies across western parts of the southern Plains, thecentral Plains and the upper Mississippi Valley to northern parts ofthe upper Great Lakes; showers and thunderstorms in eastern Texas,the lower Mississippi Valley, the Tennessee Valley and the OhioValley; showers scattered from southern parts of the upper GreatLakes across the lower Great Lakes to southern New England; freezingrain in northeast New York state and parts of northern New England;strong, gusty winds from Wyoming across the central Plains.   Predicted highs: single digits and teens from the central andnorthern Plains across the upper Mississippi Valley to upperMichigan; 20s and 30s across the Rocky Mountain region, the TexasPanhandle, much of Oklahoma, eastern Kansas and Iowa to the upperGreat Lakes, as well as northeast New York state and New England;60s and 70s in central and Southern California and southern Arizona,and from southwest Texas across eastern Texas, the lower MississippiValley, the Tennessee Valley, much of the Gulf of Mexico coast andthe southern Ohio Valley to the southern Atlantic Coast; 80s inFlorida peninsula and south-central texas.   The rest of the nation generally should have highs in the 40s and50s.   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 22 degreesbelow zero at Butte, Mont., to 76 at Key West, Fla.   Other reports:   _East: Atlanta 48 drizzle; Boston 31 cloudy; Buffalo 23 cloudy;Charleston, S.C. 55 foggy; Cincinnati 55 cloudy; Cleveland 46cloudy; Detroit 28 freezing rain; Miami 75 fair; New York 35 cloudy;Philadelphia 39 cloudy; Pittsburgh 43 cloudy; Portland, Maine 15partly cloudy; Washington 40 rain.   _Central: Bismarck 0 snow; Chicago 37 rain; Dallas-Fort Worth 46showers; Denver 2 snow; Des Moines 25 freezing drizzle; Indianapolis53 cloudy; Kansas City 22 windy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 11 snow;Nashville 54 cloudy; New Orleans 62 foggy; St. Louis 53 cloudy.   _West: Albuquerque 34 cloudy; Anchorage 17 windy; Las Vegas 41windy; Los Angeles 51 fair; Phoenix 46 fair; Salt Lake City 17 fair;San Diego 49 fair; San Francisco 44 partly cloudy; Seattle 32 fair.   _Canada: Montreal 5 cloudy; Toronto 21 cloudy.</TEXT></DOC>